# DevOps Project 1 - Linux & Command Line Basics

## 📌 Overview

This project was completed as part of the DecodeLabs DevOps Industrial Training (Batch 2026). The objective of this project is to develop a strong foundation in Linux by practicing essential command-line operations used in DevOps environments.

The project demonstrates the ability to navigate the Linux file system, manage files and directories, and perform common terminal operations without using a graphical interface.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Learn basic Linux terminal commands.
* Understand the Linux directory structure.
* Perform file and directory management.
* Practice command-line navigation.
* Build confidence in working within a Linux environment.

---

## 🛠 Skills Practiced

* Linux Terminal
* Command Line Interface (CLI)
* File Management
* Directory Management
* Linux Navigation
* Copying and Moving Files
* Removing Files and Directories
* Viewing File Contents
* Understanding File Permissions

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```text
DevOps_Project1/
